    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe default listchars `trail` char is somewhat ambiguous since it looks like a hyphen.\n\n<img width=\"226\" height=\"112\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/94ca6d29-8f77-47a8-a493-b19e74f10752\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nchange 'listchars' `trail` default to `⣿`.\n\n    :set listchars+=trail:⣿\n\n\n<img width=\"220\" height=\"107\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/baf6b3e6-829b-4556-8103-6f816eaeb272\" />",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Just as a data point, I use `vim.o.listchars = 'trail:…,nbsp:␣,tab:»·' (which are already quite annoying when having to work with other people's files...)\n\nI do recommend setting `nbsp` to something distinctive; that has saved me so much time already...",
