        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I use `trail:◘`. It's a part of CP437 and even works in Linux terminal.\n\nI also use `nbsp:◙`, which is similarly also part of CP437, although I don't usually edit files with non-breaking spaces.\n\nCP437 also has `░`, `▒` and `▓`, which look similar to the BRAILLE DOTS proposed here.",
