            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> CP437 also has `░`, `▒` and `▓`, which look similar to the BRAILLE DOTS proposed here\n\ninteresting, here's how it looks on ghostty:\n\n`░`:\n<img width=\"222\" height=\"110\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/90423d4a-e90d-41a2-8e19-1aba111d9145\" />\n\n`▒`: \n<img width=\"224\" height=\"108\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/168cc0b7-4f82-4e6a-a124-ab8c3c3e46e4\" />\n\n`▓`: \n<img width=\"219\" height=\"117\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9cda3192-3ca8-4dac-851e-61296764edc5\" />\n\n`◘`:\n<img width=\"217\" height=\"112\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6e5a4add-6d46-48c8-bcce-3f0e4414c68b\" />\n\nPersonally still favor the braille `⣿`, not sure that linux console matters that much for this.",
