        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Yeah I'll say people using neovim from the linux VT can (and for some options, probably /have/ to) do `if vim.env.TERM == \"linux\" then vim.o.listchars = '...' end`\n\nPersonally, I've seen a lot of people use interpunct (U+00B7), which incidentally also works in the linux VT, albeit with very middling visibility depending on your colors and font.",
